# Error Display Standard

- Do not render user-facing API or validation errors inline in pages (for example: `<p>{{ errorText }}</p>`).
- Surface user-facing errors via the global error modal using `useErrorModalStore().showError(...)`.
- Keep local `errorText` only for internal state/branching when needed, not for visible page text.
- For `catch` handlers, call `showError(...)` with a specific message (include status-specific copy when available).
- For shared API failures, prefer interceptor-driven modal errors and avoid duplicating inline error UI.

## Example

```ts
// ❌ Inline page error rendering pattern
errorText.value = "Unable to load messages.";

// ✅ Global modal pattern
const errorModalStore = useErrorModalStore();
errorModalStore.showError("Unable to load messages.");
```
